                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4960/54.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Leishman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-05-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Refers to Embassy’s No. 42 of May 3, and informs him that he is authorized to
                    give the adhesion of this Government to customs increase.)</p>
            </div>
